Create a new Frappe bench with a Devbox-managed environment.

Sets up a traditional bench structure (apps/, sites/) and clones frappe
plus any requested apps.

Examples:
  weg create mybench
  weg create mybench --version version-15

When to use which: 'weg create' builds a new bench; use 'weg new' for a
brand-new app, 'weg init' for an existing project, and 'weg run' to try
out an existing app.

Usage:
  weg create [bench-name] [flags]

Flags:
      --apps string      JSON of apps to initialize bench with (default "[]")
  -h, --help             help for create
      --version string   Frappe version to use (default "develop")

Global Flags:
  -C, --chdir string              Run as if weg was started in <path>
      --config string             Path to config file (default: auto-detect)
      --debug-categories string   Filter debug output: all,config,state,net,git,fs,exec
      --log-level string          Set log level: quiet, normal, verbose, debug, trace
  -o, --output string             Output format: auto, json, table, plain, quiet (default "auto")
  -q, --quiet                     Suppress non-essential output
  -v, --verbose count             Increase verbosity (-v, -vv, -vvv)
  -y, --yes                       Assume yes for all prompts
